## Impact of 200% Text Resizing
- Descriptions evaluate the effects of resizing text to 200% within a browser, focusing on content overlap and the need for lateral scrolling (3 of 3 GPT, 3 of 3 Gemini).

## Observed Layout Issues
- **Content Overlap**:
    - Resizing text to 200% reportedly caused content or elements to overlap (3 of 3 GPT), with some content being cut off (1 of 3 GPT). However, one observation noted no overlapping content occurred (1 of 3 Gemini).
- **Horizontal Scrolling**:
    - The resizing necessitated horizontal or lateral scrolling to view all content (3 of 3 GPT, 2 of 3 Gemini), potentially due to the overlapping elements (1 of 3 GPT). Conversely, one report indicated no horizontal scrolling was required (1 of 3 Gemini).
- **Component Accessibility**:
    - Despite overlap issues elsewhere, header menu elements were observed to remain accessible without overlapping in one instance (1 of 3 GPT).
